    • getClosedMinuntes

      public int getClosedMinuntes()
      Returns the number of minutes since the exchange last closed in the configured time zone. If the exchange is currently open, returns a negative value indicating the minutes remaining until the next closing time.

      The calculation accounts for:

      • Overnight closures (wrapping negative intervals into the next trading day).
      • Sunday closures (adds 24 hours to represent the weekend gap).
      • Monday pre-market period (adds 24 hours if the current time is before opening).

      Returns:
      the number of minutes since market close (positive), or negative minutes until next close if market is open
